p://pub13.ezboard.com/unownenfeared.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nown enfeared</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/01 10:16:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Dueling necros - advice please</span><hr size=1> I am a 50 rogue and would like advice for dueling a 49 necro as in what equipment and such <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uutee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Utee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/01 10:27:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Word of advice.</span><hr size=1> Dont. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aerimus>Aerimus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/01 3:12:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling necros - advice please</span><hr size=1> Don't duel him kill him )<br><br>The lvl of preparation required by a caster is a serious disadvantage.<br><br>Attack a rogue any time and he'll be ready to give ya a fight.  The only time I'm not wearing my resist gear is in groups and in that case I'll have at least an mr buff for 40-55.  A rogue unless hes soloing (rarely) is near full hp most of the time and has no manna to worry about.<br><br>A caster is at full strength if...<br>-he has the right buffs up,           not always convenient<br>-he has a pet up,                       almost never while traveling and not always when grouped<br>-he has the right spells memmed,   not always possible<br>-he has full manna and hp,            while soloing they are very vulnerable and are very often at less then                                                 full hp and especially manna  <br><br>In addition people with low hp are more vulnerable to ambush because they lose a larger percentage of their hp in the WTF period.  The 5 seconds between backstabbing them and them starting to react and fight well(not to say they will just sit there) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.13thshadowcompany.com/svimages/new_post.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/01 3:54:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/eatdonut.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling necros - advice please</span><hr size=1> Stock up on poison resist mainly, pack a few pumices for those nasty dots. Get a root poison and to make him stand still then tear through his hp's. Necro's get absolute CRAP for HP's and you can tear through them FAST. The downside is he'll be trying to tap yours away, but oh well. Tell his pet to screw off if you can (instill doubt it).<br><br>Easier said then done, but necro's do have a few disadvantages... find them, exploit them.<br><br><br> <p><center><table border=2 bordercolor="blue"><tr><td><center><b><a href="mailto:chris.painter@juno.com" border=0><font color="green">Canbik Virulentus</font></a></b><br><hr color="blue" border=2><font size=-1><font color="blue">----</font>28th Level Rogue<font color="blue">----</font><br><font color="blue">---------</font>Rallos Zek<font color="blue">---------</font><br><font color="blue">-------</font>Ring Warden<font color="blue">-------</font><br></font></center></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/01 4:50:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling necros - advice please</span><hr size=1> if you're not on a pvp server he will fear you.<br>if you are, you shouldnt have any problem.. throw on some snare poison and tear into him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukarneariethkuulcos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karne Ariethkuul COS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/01 6:20:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling necros - advice please</span><hr size=1> Dueling pet classes is always a fine line.  Pet up or no pet?  It does matter some, how many buffs is he allowed to toss on himself first?<br><br>My advice is carry pumice, up your mr, pr, and dr.  Do not fight his pet, there is no point its not like a mob pet when he dies it dies.  So go after him.  Try not to let him cast, if you are not right on him then throw a knife into him as he casts, if you are on him chances are you will disrupt his casting.<br><br>Damage shield....if you have let him buff himself this should be on him, if he is a smart necro it will be one of the last buffs he casts, because it will be harder to bring off.  If he has a damage shield down on his buff list it will be harder to bring him down.<br><br><br>Watch for DMF, if he is floating chances are you will not land poisons.  <br><br>Other than that....remember its a game and a dead necro is one who is with his @#%$.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uslinkerdread.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SlinkerDread</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/01 7:13:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling necros - advice please</span><hr size=1> Dueling Necros is not as easy as the aforementioned text. One well placed shadowstep and the rogue has a pissed off pet wailing on him, and a necro he does not know where is, that means your looking for him, hes stacking dots on you.<br><br>Slinker Assassin (60 rogue drinal)<br><br>Dreaderus (being of terror) )(Vallon Necro)<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugrimjawbadflagon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimjaw Badflagon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/01 7:44:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling necros - advice please</span><hr size=1> Its all about the terrain.<br><br>Dont duel him in a large outdoor zone.<br><br>Duel him in a noob dungeon you know well...blackburrow for instance.<br><br>You see the XXXXX casts a spell message dive in water.<br><br>Drag his pet off and kill it alone, or root it...<br><br>If he insists on dueling inlarge out door zone, if he gets shadow step off and has a pet start running taking his pet with you.<br><br>But the ideal is to whack him when hes not ready. Use some root poison,,,and pumice him before you strike to take off the damage shield.<br><br>Good luck!<br> <p><b>Grimjaw Badflagon Retired</b> <i>"cosmopolitain"</i> <b>Thug, Former Ringwarden of Terris Thule,</b><BR><b>Infinity Watch</b><BR><b>Ulster of the Shanks,  Elder Banker and Fence.(Vallon Zek)</b><BR><b>Quixote </b><BR><i><FONT COLOR=RED><FONT SIZE=2>I bought me an illusion and I put it on the wall...I let it fill my head with dreams and I had to have them all...<FONT SIZE=2></FONT COLOR=RED></i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utularthemostill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tular the Most Ill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/01 10:25:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling necros - advice please</span><hr size=1> my rule of thumb for life on a blue server... only duel casters in the freeport arena (they can't kite) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uslinkerdread.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SlinkerDread</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/15/01 7:14:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling necros - advice please</span><hr size=1> On the Zek's where you duel is an open battlefield, and casters do have some limations, particuarly, Mana limations, if they run out of mana they have no offense, and thus have to flee. ALso don't expect every fight to be a fair fight it rarely is, I cannot remember the last blue con that attempted to kill me, but RED cons always attack when your down you hae to cope with it, stick your head up and deal.<br><br>Slinker Assassin (60) Drinal<br><br>Dreaderus, being of hate, Vallon<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulirintz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lirin TZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/15/01 11:18:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling necros - advice please</span><hr size=1> aye, like slinkerdead said, on the zeks its hardly ever fair.  you get jumped, you jump them.  basically it comes down to 4 things:<br>1.  level<br>2.  skill<br>3.  preparation (mana, health, memed spells, resist equipment, etc...)<br>4.  class<br><br>imho that is the order they go in as well.  all are important, but class is less important then the others.  course, knowing their class and being prepared for it IS part of the whole preparation process. <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/drunkmonkus/CoNForever.jpg"> </p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showPrevMessage?topicID=146.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showNextMessage?topicID=146.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.emailToFriend?topicID=146.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.threadControl?topicID=146.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=146.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=146.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<option value="thesafehousefrm13">Quests of Norrath<option value="th